        <div1 type="summary">
            <p><add hand="#barker">Procedure to be followed by immigrants upon arriving in the colony.</add></p>
        </div1>
        <div1 type="body">
            

<p>"Public Notice"</p>

<p>All persons arriving in this <placeName>colony </placeName>must report themselves in
writing immediately on their arrival to the <persName>Alcalde </persName>of true district<pb n="706"/>
in which they arrive, stating the place of their birth, their present
residence, the number of their <persName>families </persName>or <persName>companions </persName>who came with
them, and their objects in visiting this country. Should they wish
to become <persName>settlers </persName>they must report themselves to me, and produce
their recommendations or other evidence of good character before
they can be allowed to select or purchase any land. Also, after this
no sales of improvements will be respected, nor will it be considered
that such sale gives to the <persName>purchaser </persName>any preference over any other
to the place purchased&#8212;actual possession is all that can secure a
preference unless a special permission is given to the contrary.</p>

<p><persName>Stephen F. Austin</persName>    [Rubric]</p>
<p><placeName>Austin's Colony</placeName> <date when="1823-10-31">October 31, 1823</date></p>

        </div1>
